'''Paul Kaznelson''' (1898&ndash;1959) was a Polish-born Czech scientist credited with describing the first case of [[pure red cell aplasia]]. He is also known for his contribution to the discovery of the therapeutic role of [[splenectomy]] in [[idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura]]. 

Much of his academic work appeared in the 1920s and 1930s, when he used to work at the [[Karl-Ferdinands-Universit<U+00E4>t|Charles University]] in [[Prague]].

